This paper is about the channel coding scheme used in the 5G standardization process, specifically polar codes concatenated with distributed cyclic redundancy check (CRC). This topic falls under the sub-categories of information theory (cs.IT), communication (cs.COMM), systems and control (cs.SY), data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), and computational complexity (cs.CC).
